Today the Minnesota High School League released their policy on Fall Sports. The Cross Country season will run on time with restrictions. Football and Volleyball have been moved to a Winter/Spring season. Football, Volleyball, and all Spring sports will be allowed to practice this fall.

Many details are still unknown. We will be getting more information out as soon as we can.

post_text:
The school has released their Summer Activities Policy for summer athletics. Workouts may begin on June 22nd to work on conditioning and scheme, the use of equipment will not be allowed at this time. We will continue to monitor the COVID situation and update restrictions as we receive more information to keep our students safe.

Each day a student plans to participate in a school activity they must complete the survey found on the top banner of the school website. To cut back on the number of people at the facilities we are only opening our summer workouts to students entering grades 9-12 at this time.

If you have any questions or would like clarification please email Sam Klaehn at sklaehn@isd500.k12.mn.us

shared_text:
Southland Music
June 18 at 11:04 AM ·

Calling all students, alumni, and community members to participate in a virtual choir for Southland Graduation 2020. The seniors have chosen 2 songs for graduation and we would like to make this tradition happen for them. The plan is to have the 2 songs played at graduation on July 17th. If you are interested in participating please email Mrs. Steinkamp jsteinkamp@isd500.k12.mn.us. message Southland Music or Mrs
Steinkamp on Facebook. Recordings have been made and a link will be sent to you if you are willing to participate. Message with what voice part or parts you are able to sing (soprano, alto, tenor, or bass). If you aren't sure what voice part you are that is okay, you can message Mrs. Steinkamp and she will help determine which voice part would be best. Directions on how to submit recordings will be sent with the practice tracks. If you have any questions please don't hesitate to ask. Hope we can all join together in song to support our graduating seniors!

Southland Education Foundation and Alumni
June 10 at 12:41 PM ·

The Southland Education Foundation would like to congratulate this year’s Southland High School Graduates and wish you all the best in pursuing your future plans and welcome you as alumni. May you hold fast to the solid foundation you have gained and earned at Southland, and use that as a stable platform in which to continue to grow, build, and give back to society by using your many gifts and talents. Your resilience and strength, as demonstrated through successfully maneuvering the challenges you’ve overcome, speak volumes to your amazing character and ability to accomplish great things in the next chapter of life!

Best Wishes to the Southland Graduating Class of 2020!

post_text: The second and third summer Senior Seminar Pre-Approval Meetings will be Tuesday June 16th from 9 am – 1 pm and Tuesday July 7th from 4 pm – 7 pm in the Rose Creek Elementary Gym- no appointment necessary, first come first served. Please enter through the bus alley doors. Bring your typed Task Analysis (parent signed) and completed pre-approval packet to the meeting. Reminder, there is a link to the recorded informational meeting that covered the pre-approval packet, expectations, and procedure on the Senior Seminar webpage (school website > middle/high > senior seminar) if needed for reference. Please contact Mrs. Mortenson or Ms. Fraser if you are unable to print the documents and/or prefer to meet via electronic meeting.

Southland Students First
May 18 at 12:25 PM ·

It is with great regret that Southland Community Education has decided to cancel all in person Community Education activities indefinitely due to safety concerns surrounding the Covid-19 pandemic. This includes Summer Rec and the Pool Bus. Drivers Training is being moved back to start August 17th and we are currently looking for ways to offer our Speed and Agility camp through a virtual medium, more information will be coming as we develop a more concrete plan.

The safety of our kids is our number one priority at this time. If we get to a point where it is determined to be safe to resume large gatherings, we will look into opening some camps and activities back up.

Sam Klaehn
Dean of Students
Southland School District
(507) 582-3568

This is how it starts..."We see your student's posters/flyers for Radon Awareness every year and have always meant to check our home and this year we finally did! Thank you as our home has high levels and we are having it mitigated."

Every year the Physical Science Class receives a message like this and it came yesterday-IT'S NOT TOO LATE! Although January has come and gone, your homes are still buttoned up for the winter months and we still have some free test kits left from Mower County Health and Human Services-just email Mrs. Mortenson and you can get one, pmortenson@isd500.k12.mn.us, or contact Mower County in the information provided below in the flyer.

PLEASE HAVE YOUR HOMES TESTED FOR RADON - IT COULD SAVE YOUR LIFE!

February 23 at 9:58 PM ·

Here is the state tournament schedule for this week. Thursday at 9am we will wrestle Blue Earth. If we lose, we'll go right away again at 11am. If we win it will be 1pm. It would be wonderful to pack the stands with fans, alumni etc from all three school districts!! This is an opportunity that doesn't happen very often so please come and support your Bulldogs! We also qualified 8 individuals with Donny and Christian placing 3rd in loaded brackets. Quite frankly it sucks as both are good enough to place as state. So, they'll be sending a message Thursday during the team tournament. Qualifiers are, Anthony Romero 106. Cohen Wiste 113. James Jacobsen 120. Lucas Winfield 132, Rece Voigt 145, Daniel Smith 160, Noah Sayles 170 and Cameron Sneed 195.

I know I'm missing people so share, tag, make calls, send emails....do whatever you can to increase our fans. We proved last week how much our kids need us, let's do it again!

post_text: A fan bus will be departing from Grand Meadow for any students or community members wanting to attend the State Wrestling meet on Thursday the 27th. Anyone interested must sign up at the office by Tuesday at noon. Cost to ride the fan bus will be $10 per person, students grade 6 or lower must be accompanied by a Chaperone. A chaperone can be a sibling grade 7-12 or an adult. Pre-sale tickets can be purchased at the Grand Meadow office, or at the door, $10 for students and $16 for adults. The meet consists of a morning session and afternoon session. If the team qualifies for the afternoon session the fan buses will be staying for session 2. Students who attend the State Wrestling Meet will be considered excused with a parent note or phone call to the school.

shared_text:
Troy Gilbert
February 9 at 7:07 PM ·

After the best regular season since 2005 your Bulldog wrestling team has earned the #1 seed in sections. We’ll wrestle Thursday night in GM at 7pm against either W-K or Triton. We’ll then wrestle Saturday in the semi finals against the winner of Chatfield/Caledonia. We need all fans there to support our efforts to get back to state for the first time in 15 seasons!! My ask of you is to make this a priority!!! Our wrestlers need and more importantly deserved to have us pack the stands as they try to win a section championship. If I coached you or your child I’m asking this as a personal favor. Our kids deserve to have the loudest cheering section in the civic center!!! Think back to when you or your child wrestled. Fan support plays a huge roll!! I better see you Saturday! Current parents and fans, make personal calls and ask for family and friends to support our team!!! Feel free to share. And remember, this is Southlands team too! Past Rebels please come and support your boys!

post_text:
Congrats to the GMLOS Wrestling Team!

The GMLOS Wrestling Team has been seeded #1 in the Section and will host a Section Wrestling Meet at the Grand Meadow High School Gym on February 13. The first round will start at 6:00 pm with Wabasha-Kellogg wrestling Triton. GMLOS will then wrestle the winner at approximately 7:15.

Ticket prices will be $7.00 for adults and $5.00 for students.
